package app

// PostBootstrap is the user-owned hook called from cmd/server.go AFTER
// Bootstrap returns and BEFORE the listener begins accepting requests.
// Its job is to wire collaborators that wire_gen cannot reach — values
// stashed on AppExtras for late binding, post-construct registrations
// onto generated worker singletons, etc.
//
// Lifecycle:
//
//  1. Bootstrap allocates *App and runs Setup (which assigns infra +
//     external clients onto App / AppExtras).
//  2. wire_gen resolves each component's Deps from App + AppExtras and
//     constructs services/workers via their `New(...)` constructors.
//  3. Bootstrap returns the populated *App.
//  4. cmd/server.go calls PostBootstrap(app) — THIS function — before
//     starting the listener or any worker. An error here aborts the
//     server boot with the returned message.
//
// Why this hook exists (vs. doing the work in Setup): wire_gen only
// runs in step 2, so collaborators that depend on a constructed
// service/worker reference (e.g. "set this snapshot saver onto the
// trader worker singleton") can't be wired before step 3. PostBootstrap
// is the single forge-blessed chokepoint for that pattern.
//
// Default body is a no-op; the user owns the file after first emit and
// forge generate will not overwrite it.
//
// To add post-bootstrap wiring:
//
//   - Read the collaborators you need off `app` (App / AppExtras fields
//     populated by Setup).
//   - Reach into the constructed component you want to extend, e.g.
//     `app.Workers.Trader.WireProductionHooks(...)`.
//   - Return any unrecoverable construction error so the boot fails
//     loudly instead of silently degrading.
//
// Canonical example — late-bound dep where worker A produces a value
// worker B needs:
//
//	func PostBootstrap(app *App) error {
//	    // SnapshotSaver is constructed by wire_gen as part of the
//	    // snapshotter worker; the trader worker can't take it in its
//	    // Deps struct (would be a construction-order cycle), so we
//	    // register it after both workers exist.
//	    saver := app.Workers.Snapshotter.SnapshotSaver()
//	    app.Workers.Trader.SetSnapshotSaver(saver)
//	    return nil
//	}
//
// Don't invent a parallel hook system (`wire_*_hooks.go`, post-Setup
// passes, etc.) for this — PostBootstrap IS that system. If you need
// late-bound coupling between a service / worker / adapter, do it here.
//
// yours: scaffolded once, never touched again — forge will not overwrite this file
//forge:allow
func PostBootstrap(app *App) error {
	_ = app
	return nil
}
